dary. The dependency arrow points one direction only: [...] `pc` is a **separate component** that, among its own concerns, happens to talk to tenex-edge across that boundary. The dependency arrow points one direction only: \n  \n ``` \n    pc ─┐ \n  Codex ─┼──▶  tenex-edge   (generic boundary: report activity / subscribe to awareness) \n    MCP ─┘                    └─ identity · awareness/board · transport (local → Nostr) \n ``` \n  \n `pc → tenex-edge`, never the reverse. If you grepped the tenex-edge codebase for "pc" you'd find nothing — and that's the test of whether the boundary is right.
